{
  "stem": "16214.3",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I don't think that every priest was like that, and I don't think-- I think that also the Roman Catholicism is changing.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And it's-- it's changing because there is, you know, the pope is different.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And it always has an idea of who is up at the helm, and what kind of things they teach you, you know.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So I think it has to do with politics, in general, world politics.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And what was incredible, I recall, when we were still in Poland in 1956, and when the Jews were fighting the Arabs, yes?",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "That was the first war.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We're still there.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And how proud the Poles were that the Jews were actually winning.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "That they would say our [NON-ENGLISH], meaning, you know, our Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It's not-- it's like diminutive.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, it's like it's so funny.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It's so funny.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I mean, I just I-- I-- I couldn't believe it at first, to hear this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But they were so really proud that these are the Jews that were from Poland, or were from close by that they were their Jews who actually won, you know, over the Arabs.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I mean, it's just-- it's crazy.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It's that the whole-- the whole idea, the whole notion is just beyond belief.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But they were so proud of their Jews, you know.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "It's-- it's very, very difficult to understand.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] what-- what can you say about it?",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I mean it's just it's-- such it's almost craziness, you know?",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I just hope that there is no prejudice.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I really genuinely hope that the prejudice should not come from either side.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I hope that Polish Roman Catholic people will have a better understanding of Jews, and-- and vice versa.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the Jews will understand Poles better.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
